reviews.review_text: Great FM Source This source sounds excellent.  This is one of the best shows of 1971, so it is very nice to have this available.  The highlights include a smoking Cumberland blues and perhaps the best NFA>GDTRFB>NFA combos played, everything is played with high energy and it worth noting this is one of Keith Godcheauxs first tours with the Dead and you can sense the fresh energy in many of the songs
Sounds great - where to torrent? This is a welcome upgrade of an all-time classic show, but I can't find it on etree.org. Saturday Night is a barn burner, and NFA>GDTRFB>NFA is one for the ages.
